130    @JsonProperty("query")
131    public void setQuery(String query) {
132        this.query = query;
133        if (StringUtils.hasText(query)) {
134            if (query.toUpperCase().startsWith("SELECT")) {
135                this.type = QueryType.SELECT;
136            }
137            if (query.toUpperCase().startsWith("CALL")) {
138                this.type = QueryType.SPROC;
139            }
140        }
141    }

154    public MapSqlParameterSource asParameterSource(MultiValueMap<String, ?> parameterValues) {
155        MapSqlParameterSource paramSource = null;
156        if (!CollectionUtils.isEmpty(parameterValues) && !getParams().isEmpty()) {
157            paramSource = new MapSqlParameterSource();
158            Set<Entry<String, String>> paramNameToParamTypeEntries = getParams().entrySet();
159            List<?> values = null;
160            for (Entry<String, String> entry : paramNameToParamTypeEntries) {
161                values = parameterValues.get(entry.getKey());
162                if (!CollectionUtils.isEmpty(values)) {
163                    if (values.size() == 1) {
164                        paramSource.addValue(entry.getKey(), parameterValues.getFirst(entry.getKey()), AttributeType.toSqlType(entry.getValue()));
165                    } else {
166                        paramSource.addValue(entry.getKey(), values);
167                    }
168                }
169            }
170        }
171        return paramSource;
172    }

175    // and parameter definition for named query is not empty
176    // will a List<SqlParameter> be constructed
177    public List<SqlParameter> asSqlParameters(MultiValueMap<String, ?> parameterValues) {
178        List<SqlParameter> sqlParams = null;
179        if (!CollectionUtils.isEmpty(parameterValues) && !getParams().isEmpty()) {
180            sqlParams = new ArrayList<>();
181            Set<Entry<String, String>> paramNameToParamTypeEntries = getParams().entrySet();
182            List<?> values = null;
183            for (Entry<String, String> entry : paramNameToParamTypeEntries) {
184                values = parameterValues.get(entry.getKey());
185                if (!CollectionUtils.isEmpty(values)) {
186                    if (values.size() == 1) {
187                        sqlParams.add(new SqlParameter(entry.getKey(), AttributeType.toSqlType(entry.getValue())));
188                    } else {
189                        throw new IllegalArgumentException("Stored Procedure cannot be executed! Parameter [%s] is not a scalar value!".formatted(entry.getKey()));
190                    }
191                }
192            }
193        }
194        return sqlParams;
